import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import yfinance as yf
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from statsmodels.tsa.stattools import adfuller, coint
from statsmodels.tsa.arima.model import ARIMA
import warnings
warnings.filterwarnings("ignore")

# Set random seed for reproducibility
np.random.seed(42)

# Step 1: Fetch stock data for KO and PEP
start_date = "2020-01-01"
end_date = "2025-02-28"

print("Fetching data for KO (Coca-Cola)...")
ko_data = yf.download("KO", start=start_date, end=end_date)
print("Fetching data for PEP (PepsiCo)...")
pep_data = yf.download("PEP", start=start_date, end=end_date)

# Extract 'Close' prices
ko_prices = ko_data["Close"].dropna()
pep_prices = pep_data["Close"].dropna()

# Align indices (in case of mismatched trading days)
combined = pd.concat([ko_prices, pep_prices], axis=1).dropna()
ko_prices = combined.iloc[:, 0]
pep_prices = combined.iloc[:, 1]

print("KO Prices Head:\n", ko_prices.head())
print("PEP Prices Head:\n", pep_prices.head())

# Step 2: Simulate a Random Walk
def random_walk_simulation(initial_price, steps, scale=1):
    random_steps = np.random.normal(loc=0, scale=scale, size=steps)
    random_steps[0] = 0
    return initial_price + np.cumsum(random_steps)

ko_rw = random_walk_simulation(ko_prices.iloc[0], len(ko_prices), scale=2)
pep_rw = random_walk_simulation(pep_prices.iloc[0], len(pep_prices), scale=2)

# Step 3: Unit Root Test (ADF)
def unit_root_test(series, name):
    result = adfuller(series.dropna())
    print(f"\nUnit Root Test (ADF) for {name}:")
    print(f"ADF Statistic: {result[0]:.4f}")
    print(f"p-value: {result[1]:.4f}")
    print("Critical Values:", {k: round(v, 4) for k, v in result[4].items()})
    if result[1] > 0.05:
        print(f"{name} likely has a unit root (non-stationary).")
    else:
        print(f"{name} does not have a unit root (stationary).")

ko_returns = ko_prices.pct_change().dropna()
pep_returns = pep_prices.pct_change().dropna()

unit_root_test(ko_prices, "KO Prices")
unit_root_test(pep_prices, "PEP Prices")
unit_root_test(ko_returns, "KO Returns")
unit_root_test(pep_returns, "PEP Returns")

# Step 4: Cointegration Test (Engle-Granger)
print("\nCointegration Test (Engle-Granger) between KO and PEP:")
coint_result = coint(ko_prices, pep_prices)
print(f"Cointegration t-statistic: {coint_result[0]:.4f}")
print(f"p-value: {coint_result[1]:.4f}")
# Handle critical values as an array
critical_values = {"1%": coint_result[2][0], "5%": coint_result[2][1], "10%": coint_result[2][2]}
print("Critical Values:", {k: round(v, 4) for k, v in critical_values.items()})
if coint_result[1] < 0.05:
    print("KO and PEP are likely cointegrated.")
else:
    print("KO and PEP are not cointegrated.")

# Step 5: Fit ARMA Model (ARMA(1,1))
def fit_arma(series, name):
    model = ARIMA(series, order=(1, 0, 1))
    fit = model.fit()
    print(f"\nARMA(1,1) Model Summary for {name}:")
    print(fit.summary().tables[1])
    return fit

ko_arma = fit_arma(ko_returns, "KO Returns")
pep_arma = fit_arma(pep_returns, "PEP Returns")

# Step 6: Plotting
plt.figure(figsize=(14, 10))

# Random Walk vs Actual Prices
plt.subplot(3, 1, 1)
plt.plot(ko_prices.index, ko_prices, label="KO Actual", color="blue")
plt.plot(ko_prices.index, ko_rw, label="KO Random Walk", color="orange", linestyle="--")
plt.plot(pep_prices.index, pep_prices, label="PEP Actual", color="green")
plt.plot(pep_prices.index, pep_rw, label="PEP Random Walk", color="red", linestyle="--")
plt.title("Stock Prices vs Random Walk Simulation (KO and PEP)")
plt.xlabel("Date")
plt.ylabel("Price (USD)")
plt.legend()

# Returns
plt.subplot(3, 1, 2)
plt.plot(ko_returns.index, ko_returns, label="KO Returns", color="blue")
plt.plot(pep_returns.index, pep_returns, label="PEP Returns", color="green")
plt.title("Daily Returns (KO and PEP)")
plt.xlabel("Date")
plt.ylabel("Returns")
plt.legend()

# ARMA Forecasts (last 30 days)
ko_forecast = ko_arma.forecast(steps=30)
pep_forecast = pep_arma.forecast(steps=30)
forecast_index = pd.date_range(start=ko_returns.index[-1], periods=30, freq="B")

plt.subplot(3, 1, 3)
plt.plot(ko_returns.index[-30:], ko_returns[-30:], label="KO Actual Returns", color="blue")
plt.plot(forecast_index, ko_forecast, label="KO ARMA Forecast", color="orange", linestyle="--")
plt.plot(pep_returns.index[-30:], pep_returns[-30:], label="PEP Actual Returns", color="green")
plt.plot(forecast_index, pep_forecast, label="PEP ARMA Forecast", color="red", linestyle="--")
plt.title("ARMA(1,1) Forecast vs Actual Returns (Last 30 Days)")
plt.xlabel("Date")
plt.ylabel("Returns")
plt.legend()

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# Install required libraries in Colab
!pip install yfinance statsmodels matplotlib pandas numpy

import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import yfinance as yf
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from statsmodels.tsa.stattools import adfuller, coint
from statsmodels.tsa.arima.model import ARIMA
import warnings
warnings.filterwarnings("ignore")

# Set random seed for reproducibility
np.random.seed(42)

# Step 1: Fetch stock data for SPY and DIA
start_date = "2020-01-01"
end_date = "2025-02-28"

print("Fetching data for SPY (S&P 500 ETF)...")
spy_data = yf.download("SPY", start=start_date, end=end_date)
print("Fetching data for DIA (Dow Jones ETF)...")
dia_data = yf.download("DIA", start=start_date, end=end_date)

# Extract 'Close' prices
spy_prices = spy_data["Close"].dropna()
dia_prices = dia_data["Close"].dropna()

# Align indices (in case of mismatched trading days)
combined = pd.concat([spy_prices, dia_prices], axis=1).dropna()
spy_prices = combined.iloc[:, 0]
dia_prices = combined.iloc[:, 1]

print("SPY Prices Head:\n", spy_prices.head())
print("DIA Prices Head:\n", dia_prices.head())

# Step 2: Simulate a Random Walk
def random_walk_simulation(initial_price, steps, scale=1):
    random_steps = np.random.normal(loc=0, scale=scale, size=steps)
    random_steps[0] = 0
    return initial_price + np.cumsum(random_steps)

spy_rw = random_walk_simulation(spy_prices.iloc[0], len(spy_prices), scale=2)
dia_rw = random_walk_simulation(dia_prices.iloc[0], len(dia_prices), scale=2)

# Step 3: Unit Root Test (ADF)
def unit_root_test(series, name):
    result = adfuller(series.dropna())
    print(f"\nUnit Root Test (ADF) for {name}:")
    print(f"ADF Statistic: {result[0]:.4f}")
    print(f"p-value: {result[1]:.4f}")
    print("Critical Values:", {k: round(v, 4) for k, v in result[4].items()})
    if result[1] > 0.05:
        print(f"{name} likely has a unit root (non-stationary).")
    else:
        print(f"{name} does not have a unit root (stationary).")

spy_returns = spy_prices.pct_change().dropna()
dia_returns = dia_prices.pct_change().dropna()

unit_root_test(spy_prices, "SPY Prices")
unit_root_test(dia_prices, "DIA Prices")
unit_root_test(spy_returns, "SPY Returns")
unit_root_test(dia_returns, "DIA Returns")

# Step 4: Cointegration Test (Engle-Granger)
print("\nCointegration Test (Engle-Granger) between SPY and DIA:")
coint_result = coint(spy_prices, dia_prices)
print(f"Cointegration t-statistic: {coint_result[0]:.4f}")
print(f"p-value: {coint_result[1]:.4f}")
critical_values = {"1%": coint_result[2][0], "5%": coint_result[2][1], "10%": coint_result[2][2]}
print("Critical Values:", {k: round(v, 4) for k, v in critical_values.items()})
if coint_result[1] < 0.05:
    print("SPY and DIA are likely cointegrated.")
else:
    print("SPY and DIA are not cointegrated.")

# Step 5: Fit ARMA Model (ARMA(1,1))
def fit_arma(series, name):
    model = ARIMA(series, order=(1, 0, 1))
    fit = model.fit()
    print(f"\nARMA(1,1) Model Summary for {name}:")
    print(fit.summary().tables[1])
    return fit

spy_arma = fit_arma(spy_returns, "SPY Returns")
dia_arma = fit_arma(dia_returns, "DIA Returns")

# Step 6: Plotting
plt.figure(figsize=(14, 10))

# Random Walk vs Actual Prices
plt.subplot(3, 1, 1)
plt.plot(spy_prices.index, spy_prices, label="SPY Actual", color="blue")
plt.plot(spy_prices.index, spy_rw, label="SPY Random Walk", color="orange", linestyle="--")
plt.plot(dia_prices.index, dia_prices, label="DIA Actual", color="green")
plt.plot(dia_prices.index, dia_rw, label="DIA Random Walk", color="red", linestyle="--")
plt.title("Stock Prices vs Random Walk Simulation (SPY and DIA)")
plt.xlabel("Date")
plt.ylabel("Price (USD)")
plt.legend()

# Returns
plt.subplot(3, 1, 2)
plt.plot(spy_returns.index, spy_returns, label="SPY Returns", color="blue")
plt.plot(dia_returns.index, dia_returns, label="DIA Returns", color="green")
plt.title("Daily Returns (SPY and DIA)")
plt.xlabel("Date")
plt.ylabel("Returns")
plt.legend()

# ARMA Forecasts (last 30 days)
spy_forecast = spy_arma.forecast(steps=30)
dia_forecast = dia_arma.forecast(steps=30)
forecast_index = pd.date_range(start=spy_returns.index[-1], periods=30, freq="B")

plt.subplot(3, 1, 3)
plt.plot(spy_returns.index[-30:], spy_returns[-30:], label="SPY Actual Returns", color="blue")
plt.plot(forecast_index, spy_forecast, label="SPY ARMA Forecast", color="orange", linestyle="--")
plt.plot(dia_returns.index[-30:], dia_returns[-30:], label="DIA Actual Returns", color="green")
plt.plot(forecast_index, dia_forecast, label="DIA ARMA Forecast", color="red", linestyle="--")
plt.title("ARMA(1,1) Forecast vs Actual Returns (Last 30 Days)")
plt.xlabel("Date")
plt.ylabel("Returns")
plt.legend()

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
